1
00:00:00,690 --> 00:00:06,220
Let’s consider that the market suddenly
makes a large movement in one direction.

2
00:00:06,220 --> 00:00:11,169
Perhaps this movement is in response to new
information coming into the market, or it

3
00:00:11,169 --> 00:00:14,739
can simply be a result of a random price spike.

4
00:00:14,739 --> 00:00:20,990
No matter the reason behind the price fluctuation,
this type of sharp movement is called a momentum

5
00:00:20,990 --> 00:00:21,990
move.

6
00:00:21,990 --> 00:00:24,170
This means that the market accelerated.

7
00:00:24,170 --> 00:00:28,930
As the price movement starts to slow down,
the momentum will also slow down.

8
00:00:28,930 --> 00:00:34,890
Now, wouldn’t be ideal if you entered when
the market momentum was increasing?

9
00:00:34,890 --> 00:00:39,579
Of course, when you have momentum on your
side, trading becomes easy.

10
00:00:39,579 --> 00:00:44,530
When you enter during a lack of momentum,
your trade will stagnate or even worse, you

11
00:00:44,530 --> 00:00:47,289
will get chopped out by lateral price movement.

12
00:00:47,289 --> 00:00:52,639
That’s why today we’ll talk about momentum
indicator and you’ll learn how to take signals

13
00:00:52,639 --> 00:00:57,570
in order to synchronize with the market when
is ready to make a significant move.

14
00:00:57,570 --> 00:01:02,519
Also, make sure you subscribe, click the bell
icon so you don’t miss our future uploads,

15
00:01:02,519 --> 00:01:06,040
and leave us a like to show your support.

16
00:01:06,040 --> 00:01:10,400
Momentum indicator is an oscillator which
identifies the strength or speed of a price

17
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:11,500
movement.

18
00:01:11,500 --> 00:01:17,000
The momentum indicator compares the most recent
price to a previously determined price and

19
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:19,940
measures the velocity of the price change.

20
00:01:19,940 --> 00:01:24,110
So basically is the difference between the
most recent price and the closing price of

21
00:01:24,110 --> 00:01:28,950
a previously determined period,
The faster the price increases, the bigger

22
00:01:28,950 --> 00:01:34,640
the increase in momentum indicator
The faster the price decreases, the bigger

23
00:01:34,640 --> 00:01:38,550
the decrease in momentum indicator

24
00:01:38,550 --> 00:01:44,500
The most used settings for the momentum indicator
are 7, 14, or 21.

25
00:01:44,500 --> 00:01:50,040
Momentum settings with values over 21 make
the indicator less sensitive.

26
00:01:50,040 --> 00:01:56,280
This will result in fewer, but better quality
signals and a smoother line of the indicator

27
00:01:56,280 --> 00:02:00,970
Momentum settings with values below 10 make
the indicator oversensitive.

28
00:02:00,970 --> 00:02:05,030
This will result in more market noise.

29
00:02:05,030 --> 00:02:10,670
Lower settings on the momentum indicator should
be carefully traded, as it can lead to many

30
00:02:10,670 --> 00:02:13,140
false signals.

31
00:02:13,140 --> 00:02:17,130
Here is how you should read the momentum indicator
when you analyze the trend:

32
00:02:17,130 --> 00:02:23,840
If the momentum indicator is above 0 level,
this signals that the market bias is on the

33
00:02:23,840 --> 00:02:27,819
upside
If the momentum indicator is above 0 level

34
00:02:27,819 --> 00:02:33,030
and the market price is increasing, this signals
that the trend is accelerating.

35
00:02:33,030 --> 00:02:39,090
This implies that the current upward trend
is strong and likely to continue.

36
00:02:39,090 --> 00:02:45,220
If the momentum indicator starts declining
but is still above the 0 level, this means

37
00:02:45,220 --> 00:02:50,060
that the trend is still on the upside, but
at a reduced rate.

38
00:02:50,060 --> 00:02:53,900
This signals that the market is losing upward
momentum.

39
00:02:53,900 --> 00:02:59,020
This doesn’t mean that a reversal or trend
change will happen, it’s just a warning

40
00:02:59,020 --> 00:03:03,150
sign that the momentum is getting weaker.

41
00:03:03,150 --> 00:03:08,090
If the momentum indicator is below 0 level,
this signals that the market bias is on the

42
00:03:08,090 --> 00:03:11,910
downside
If the momentum indicator is below 0 level

43
00:03:11,910 --> 00:03:17,410
and the market price is decreasing, this signals
that the downtrend is accelerating.

44
00:03:17,410 --> 00:03:22,180
This means that the current downtrend trend
is strong and likely to continue.

45
00:03:22,180 --> 00:03:27,349
If the momentum indicator starts increasing
but is still below the 0 level, this means

46
00:03:27,349 --> 00:03:32,810
that the trend is still on the downside, but
at a reduced rate and signals that the market

47
00:03:32,810 --> 00:03:35,569
is losing downward momentum.

48
00:03:35,569 --> 00:03:40,680
As in the case of an uptrend, this does not
mean that a reversal or trend change will

49
00:03:40,680 --> 00:03:41,680
happen.

50
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:46,350
Ok, now let’s see how to trade with momentum
indicator.

51
00:03:46,350 --> 00:03:51,270
One of the most common ways in which traders
use the momentum indicator, but not the smart

52
00:03:51,270 --> 00:03:56,120
way, is to take signals when the oscillator
crosses the 0 level.

53
00:03:56,120 --> 00:04:00,690
When momentum indicator crosses above zero,
a buy signal is generated

54
00:04:00,690 --> 00:04:05,400
When momentum indicator crosses below zero,
a sell signal is generated

55
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:12,190
If we analyze this tesla chart, we might get
fooled by the last 2 valid signals generated

56
00:04:12,190 --> 00:04:13,910
by the momentum indicator.

57
00:04:13,910 --> 00:04:21,019
As most indicators, during trending conditions,
the indicator will offer good signals.

58
00:04:21,019 --> 00:04:25,030
But what about when markets are not trending?

59
00:04:25,030 --> 00:04:26,620
Look at this.

60
00:04:26,620 --> 00:04:32,270
You can see at least 4 or 5 false signals
which would have damaged your account.

61
00:04:32,270 --> 00:04:38,220
Despite the fact we are analyzing the d1 chart,
we can clearly see that the indicator is not

62
00:04:38,220 --> 00:04:42,139
reliable for generating good signals when
used alone.

63
00:04:42,139 --> 00:04:47,580
So, you should never use momentum as a standalone
tool.

64
00:04:47,580 --> 00:04:52,770
Pay attention to key levels, identify the
major areas of support and resistance and

65
00:04:52,770 --> 00:04:58,150
use momentum as an additional confirmation
instrument, to confirm your bias.

66
00:04:58,150 --> 00:05:04,830
Now, let’s look at the same chart once again,
let’s plot the support and resistance lines,

67
00:05:04,830 --> 00:05:10,470
identify the trend using price action and
let’s see what the momentum is telling.

68
00:05:10,470 --> 00:05:17,190
So we are in a clear downtrend, with the price
making lower lows and lower highs.

69
00:05:17,190 --> 00:05:22,720
This tells me to ignore when the momentum
crosses the 0 line to the upside and focus

70
00:05:22,720 --> 00:05:24,169
only on short trades.

71
00:05:24,169 --> 00:05:29,260
Good, now let’s plot major support and resistance
lines.

72
00:05:29,260 --> 00:05:32,990
Here is the most important trade, our entry
point.

73
00:05:32,990 --> 00:05:39,010
We have a breakout of a key support line,
with the retest of the breakout level and

74
00:05:39,010 --> 00:05:42,190
the momentum staying below 0 line.

75
00:05:42,190 --> 00:05:51,100
A short around this area was a high probability
trade, because we had price action and momentum

76
00:05:51,100 --> 00:05:52,820
indicating the same thing.

77
00:05:52,820 --> 00:05:56,540
The momentum oscillator can also detect divergences.

78
00:05:56,540 --> 00:06:02,620
A divergence occurs when price action differs
from the evolution of momentum oscillator.

79
00:06:02,620 --> 00:06:07,680
This basically means that the momentum isn’t
reflected in the price, which could be an

80
00:06:07,680 --> 00:06:10,340
early indicator of a reversal.

81
00:06:10,340 --> 00:06:16,640
As in the case of stochastic or rsi oscillators,
when a divergence occurs, a potential change

82
00:06:16,640 --> 00:06:19,920
in price direction could be on the cards.

83
00:06:19,920 --> 00:06:23,360
This is how i spot divergences with the momentum
indicator:

84
00:06:23,360 --> 00:06:28,790
I like to determine the main trend by adding
a 200-period exponential moving average.

85
00:06:28,790 --> 00:06:32,420
When the price trades above the 200-period
exponential moving average, i consider taking

86
00:06:32,420 --> 00:06:37,389
only long entries and when the price trades
below the 200-period exponential moving average

87
00:06:37,389 --> 00:06:40,240
i enter only short entries.

88
00:06:40,240 --> 00:06:45,650
I search for divergences between the momentum
and the price only in the direction of the

89
00:06:45,650 --> 00:06:49,320
main trend indicated by the 200-period exponential
moving average

90
00:06:49,320 --> 00:06:56,400
So, if the price trades above the 200 EMA,
I search for divergences on the lower side

91
00:06:56,400 --> 00:07:02,419
of the momentum indicator and if the price
trades below the 200 EMA, we search for divergences

92
00:07:02,419 --> 00:07:05,100
on the upper side of the momentum indicator.

93
00:07:05,100 --> 00:07:11,150
I enter when i spot a divergence in the direction
of the trend, when the momentum crosses below

94
00:07:11,150 --> 00:07:13,080
or above the 0 line.

95
00:07:13,080 --> 00:07:18,210
Also, if you aren’t familiar with divergences,
i recommend you to watch this video after

96
00:07:18,210 --> 00:07:19,800
you finish this one.

97
00:07:19,800 --> 00:07:25,180
Let’s use the same tesla stock, this time
on the hourly time frame.

98
00:07:25,180 --> 00:07:33,620
We added the 200 EMA, the price is below it,
lower lows and lower highs, so a clear downtrend.

99
00:07:33,620 --> 00:07:38,210
We search for divergences on the upper side
of momentum.

100
00:07:38,210 --> 00:07:44,190
Here is a first divergence, the price making
higher highs and momentum indicating lower

101
00:07:44,190 --> 00:07:45,190
highs.

102
00:07:45,190 --> 00:07:48,479
You enter short when the momentum crosses
below 0 line.

103
00:07:48,479 --> 00:07:53,080
Here’s a hidden divergence.

104
00:07:53,080 --> 00:07:59,270
The price is making lower highs but the momentum
shows higher highs.

105
00:07:59,270 --> 00:08:03,080
You enter when the momentum crosses the 0
line.

106
00:08:03,080 --> 00:08:05,680
You see how important this rule is.

107
00:08:05,680 --> 00:08:08,310
You cannot enter just because you see a divergence.

108
00:08:08,310 --> 00:08:10,509
The price could increase even more.

109
00:08:10,509 --> 00:08:15,990
By waiting for the 0-line cross, you have
a protection buffer, and enter only if the

110
00:08:15,990 --> 00:08:18,340
downward momentum is strong.

111
00:08:18,340 --> 00:08:25,600
Also, i know you will be tempted to take regular
divergences on the lower side of the momentum.

112
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:32,149
I noticed this divergence here, and yes, it
was a good divergence trade and another one

113
00:08:32,149 --> 00:08:38,950
here, with a potential entry here, a perfect
trade, almost catching the market bottom.

114
00:08:38,950 --> 00:08:45,610
However, I trained myself to ignore the signals
that aren’t in line with the main trend.

115
00:08:45,610 --> 00:08:49,890
I lost a lot of money entering countertrend
positions.

116
00:08:49,890 --> 00:08:55,801
This technique will save you a lot of bad
entries, which at the end of the day, are

117
00:08:55,801 --> 00:08:58,170
contrary to the primary trend.

118
00:08:58,170 --> 00:09:04,149
I want to ride the main trend, and all the
setups that occur in the opposite direction

119
00:09:04,149 --> 00:09:06,550
will be ignored.

120
00:09:06,550 --> 00:09:10,790
In order to smooth the signals offered by
the momentum indicator, many traders prefer

121
00:09:10,790 --> 00:09:16,390
to add a moving average on it, like in the
case of the RSI, to take crossover signals.

122
00:09:16,390 --> 00:09:21,750
Now, when you want to trade a crossover between
the momentum oscillator and a moving average,

123
00:09:21,750 --> 00:09:27,250
you should be aware a crossover will be effective
when markets are trending.

124
00:09:27,250 --> 00:09:32,120
When markets are trading in a range, this
system will not work.

125
00:09:32,120 --> 00:09:37,610
This problem can be diminished by once again
responding only to signals in the trending

126
00:09:37,610 --> 00:09:39,180
direction.

127
00:09:39,180 --> 00:09:45,810
In this case, if the trend is up, make a long
trade only after the indicator has moved above

128
00:09:45,810 --> 00:09:48,120
the moving average.

129
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:53,770
I still prefer the 0 line cross in combination
with price action, but you could test different

130
00:09:53,770 --> 00:09:59,310
moving average periods and momentum indicator
settings to find a combination that works

131
00:09:59,310 --> 00:10:01,460
for your trading style.

132
00:10:01,460 --> 00:10:06,610
If you found value or learned something new,
don’t forget to subscribe, click the notification

133
00:10:06,610 --> 00:10:09,949
icon and leave a like to show your support.

